Jaroslav Volek (15 July 1923, Trenčín – 23 February 1989, Prague) was a Czech musicologist, semiotician who developed a theory of modal music.
He wrote General Theory of Art based on semiotic concepts in 1968.
Late in his life he was allowed to travel, and was a guest at American University during the 1980s.
What this means is that components dominate their moment, but the joining of components—notes, chords, melodic themes—produces the shape and tension in a work.
